column9: videos where the ball get hit by a player are more important because they make you want to keep watching what happens next
I made one error, on the first 3 second video, I meant to put agree. If it was gameplay and not a cinematic clip, then I thought it was important
If the content of the video was interesting/important to understand the video, or not
If it showed the result of the play
How interesting the clip was as well as how important to the overall video I considered it to be
The one that scored a goal.
whether it led to something a fan would think is important, like a missed goal, or disappointed player
Whether or not I'd seen the main goal.
if it was a view of the ball getting close to the goal
If it was a missed goal or goal attempt I thought it would be important.
If it has any important event.
What impact the action had on the attempt to make a goal and failure to do so
if the action was around the goal or showed something that lead to a goal
It depended on the relevance to the scene in regards to the game
ACTION TAKING PLACE AT THAT INSTANCE IN THE VIDEO
whether something important happen in correlation to the events of the video
I figure the most important part of the clip was the shot on goal.  If it related to that and was important to setting up the shot - it was important.
I selected the videos that had to do with the missed goal mainly.  Not the ones that were just showing the playing leading up or after the missed shot.
I really looked at what was happening in each clip.
The clips where they were just moving the ball around I deemed unimportant. That's just average soccer and unrelated to the missed goal.
If it showed something important like a goal or missing a goal.
The goal kick prior and after
